  "body": "If you use embed fonts for text like War and Peace with russian and french characters and you programmatically scroll bottom after component was rendered (componentDidMount) you will have excess gap in the bottom of scrolling.\r\n\r\n![react_bug](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2244675/21029933/1294fd8a-bdad-11e6-941c-99d1d7199b5c.png)\r\n[Example](http://run.plnkr.co/ZJ5Dvh4frCYB9PfC), [code](http://plnkr.co/edit/aOKAp0En9QoELQPrPRib?p=preview) (use separate window mode in Plnker editor if example dosn't work)\r\n\r\nMaybe it is because React rendering doesn't conform with fonts rendering\r\n\r\nReact .., 14, 15; Chrome, Firefox; Windows 10, Ubuntu 16\r\n\r\n",
